SIMPLE: summary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Summary
<hw>Sum"ma*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sommaire</ets>. See <er>Sum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed
into a sum; summed up; reduced into a narrow compass, or into few words;
short; brief; concise; compendious; <as>as, a <ex>summary</ex> statement
of facts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, rapidly performed; quickly executed; <as>as,
a <ex>summary</ex> process; to take <ex>summary</ex>
vengeance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Short; brief; concise; compendious;
succinct.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Summary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Summary
<hw>Sum"ma*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Summaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>sommaire</ets>,
or L. <ets>summarium</ets>. See <er>Summary</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A general or comprehensive statement; an abridged account; an
abstract, abridgment, or compendium, containing the sum or substance of
a fuller account.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Summation</ent>⟦br⟧
